Docs.summary: Specifies the unique identifier of the task in the Published.database.

remarks.para: Project Server isolates a team member's status changes until they are approved by the project manager. When a team member saves the status of an assignment, Project Server creates a working copy of the task with the assignment changes in the MSP_TASKS_SAVED table. The working copy has a unique , but the TASK_PUBLISHED_UID is the same as the TASK_UID in the MSP_TASKS table. The same process occurs in the MSP_TASKS_SUBMITTED table when the team member submits the status for approval. When the project manager approves the status, the changes are applied to the task in the MSP_TASKS table.
